{
  "stem": "22840.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He was an ophthalmologist in Haifa later on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] And they gave me a name.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They gave me a cover story that they invented on the spot, immediately, the first time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The named me Jan-- kind of obvious.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "There was another Jan there, but they knew  a Jan-- or John-- is a very, very, very standard name in Slovakia, Jan.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And my last name was Suchy, which means, in Slovak means dry.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I finally came out and be dry and-- and warm.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So my name was Jan Suchy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But what's more important to show how-- how these very primitive people were-- were very intelligent in the sense of life intelligence, life smarts-- they taught me immediately a prayer, a Christian prayer.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They say, we will teach you, and they said the name of the prayer.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And for me, the name of the prayer had no meaning.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They say we will teach you Otche Nash.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "It's not a-- it's not a Slovak word, octche nash.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I didn't recognize it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Only many, many, many years later-- only many years later, when I became interested in religions, I realized that otche nash is not one word.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "It's two words, which is Otche Nash, which is Our Father, which is the beginning of the basic Christian our Father in heaven, the sermon of the mount prayer-- the basic prayer of-- of Christianity.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And they taught me that because the Germans would ask children to recite the Otche Nash, and if you didn't know it, you were Jewish, and you were shot.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] If you didn't know it, if you were not Jewish, you were shot anyway, but that's-- that's another story.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Christian children knew our Father in Heaven.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "It was taught with them.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
